Articles.Content:
What do you want to change in there ? 

The global node (the check for Ore is important because an other mod could add something else)

    @GLOBAL_RESOURCE:HAS[#ResourceName[Ore]]{		@Distribution	{		@PresenceChance = 90	}}

A PLANETARY\_RESOURCE nodes :

    @PLANETARY_RESOURCE:HAS[#PlanetName[Eve],#BiomeName[Explodium?Sea]]{  @Distribution  {     @PresenceChance = 2  }}

And if you want to add a config for a specific planet/biome you just add them in your cfg if they are not already in the stock file

    BIOME_RESOURCE{	ResourceName = Ore	ResourceType = 0	PlanetName = Duna	BiomeName = Pole	Distribution	{		PresenceChance = 0		MinAbundance = 0		MaxAbundance = 0		Variance = 0		Dispersal = 0	}}
